## FRONTEND CODING RULES

### Component Rules
- ALWAYS use TypeScript interfaces for props
- ALWAYS handle loading state
- ALWAYS handle error state  
- ALWAYS handle empty state
- NEVER use any type in TypeScript
- ALWAYS use const over let where possible
- ALWAYS cleanup useEffect subscriptions
- NEVER call API directly in JSX render
- ALWAYS use custom hooks for API calls

### Form Handling Pattern
Always follow this pattern for forms:
  const [formData, setFormData] = useState({...})
  const [errors, setErrors] = useState({})
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false)
  
  const validate = () => {
    const newErrors = {}
    if (!formData.email) newErrors.email = 'Email required'
    if (!formData.password) newErrors.password = 'Password required'
    setErrors(newErrors)
    return Object.keys(newErrors).length === 0
  }
  
  const handleSubmit = async () => {
    if (!validate()) return // stop if invalid
    setLoading(true)
    try {
      const res = await fetch(...)
      const data = await res.json()
      if (!res.ok) {
        // Handle field-specific errors from API
        if (data.field) {
          setErrors({ [data.field]: data.error })
        } else {
          toast.error(data.error || 'Something went wrong')
        }
        return
      }
      // success
    } catch (error) {
      toast.error('Network error. Please try again.')
    } finally {
      setLoading(false)
    }
  }

### API Call Pattern
Always use this pattern:
  const [data, setData] = useState(null)
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true)
  const [error, setError] = useState(null)
  
  useEffect(() => {
    let cancelled = false // prevent memory leaks
    
    const fetchData = async () => {
      try {
        setLoading(true)
        setError(null)
        const res = await fetch(url, {
          headers: {
            'Content-Type': 'application/json',
            ...(token ? { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` } : {})
          }
        })
        if (!res.ok) throw new Error(await res.text())
        const json = await res.json()
        if (!cancelled) setData(json)
      } catch (err) {
        if (!cancelled) setError(err.message)
      } finally {
        if (!cancelled) setLoading(false)
      }
    }
    
    fetchData()
    return () => { cancelled = true } // cleanup
  }, [url])

### UI/UX Rules
- ALWAYS show loading spinner on async actions
- ALWAYS disable buttons while loading (prevent double submit)
- ALWAYS show inline error messages under fields
- ALWAYS show success feedback after actions
- ALWAYS confirm before destructive actions (delete)
- ALWAYS show empty states with helpful message + action
- NEVER show raw error messages to users
- ALWAYS show character count on text areas
- ALWAYS auto-focus first input in forms/modals

