## DESIGN RULES

### Golden Lotus Design System
Primary color: #F97316 (orange)
Background: #FFFFFF (white)
Text: #111827 (gray-900)
Subtext: #6B7280 (gray-500)
Border: #E5E7EB (gray-200)
Error: #DC2626 (red-500)
Success: #16A34A (green-500)
Warning: #F59E0B (amber-500)

### Component Design Standards
- Buttons: rounded-xl (12px), min height 44px (touch friendly)
- Inputs: rounded-lg, border, focus:ring-orange-500
- Cards: rounded-2xl, shadow-sm, border border-gray-100
- Modals: rounded-2xl, shadow-xl, backdrop blur
- Always 8px grid spacing (multiples of 2/4/8)
- Mobile first: design for 375px then scale up

### Accessibility Rules
- ALWAYS add aria-label to icon buttons
- ALWAYS add alt text to images
- ALWAYS use semantic HTML (button not div)
- ALWAYS ensure 4.5:1 color contrast ratio
- ALWAYS support keyboard navigation
- ALWAYS add focus visible styles

---

## SCALABILITY RULES

### Code Organization
- ONE component = ONE responsibility
- NEVER put business logic in UI components
- ALWAYS extract reusable logic to custom hooks
- ALWAYS extract API calls to service files
- ALWAYS use constants for magic numbers/strings
- NEVER hardcode URLs, use environment variables

### Multi-Restaurant Ready
- ALWAYS include restaurantId in queries (future SaaS)
- ALWAYS use dynamic config (no hardcoded restaurant name)
- ALWAYS store config in database not code
- Design every feature to work for N restaurants

### Performance Patterns
- ALWAYS lazy load routes:
  const Menu = lazy(() => import('./pages/Menu'))
- ALWAYS memoize expensive components:
  export default memo(HeavyComponent)
- ALWAYS debounce search inputs (500ms)
- ALWAYS use optimistic updates for better UX
- ALWAYS implement virtual scrolling for long lists
- ALWAYS cache API responses where appropriate

---

## CODE QUALITY RULES

### Before Writing Any Code
1. Understand the full requirement
2. Think about edge cases
3. Think about error states
4. Think about security implications
5. Think about performance impact
6. Then write the code

### Code Review Checklist
Before finishing any task check:
  ✅ All inputs validated (frontend + backend)
  ✅ Auth checked on protected endpoints
  ✅ Error handling in try/catch
  ✅ Loading states handled
  ✅ Empty states handled
  ✅ No console.logs with sensitive data
  ✅ No hardcoded secrets
  ✅ TypeScript types defined
  ✅ Mobile responsive
  ✅ Accessibility basics met

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (MenuItemCard)
- Functions: camelCase (handleSubmit)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE (MAX_RETRIES)
- Files: kebab-case (menu-item-card.tsx)
- DB collections: camelCase plural (menuItems)
- API actions: kebab-case (add-favorite)
- CSS classes: Tailwind only (no custom CSS)

### TypeScript Rules
- NEVER use any type
- ALWAYS define interface for:
  - Component props
  - API request bodies
  - API response shapes
  - Database documents
- ALWAYS use enums for fixed values:
  enum OrderStatus {
    PENDING = 'pending',
    CONFIRMED = 'confirmed',
    PREPARING = 'preparing',
    READY = 'ready',
    COMPLETED = 'completed',
    CANCELLED = 'cancelled'
  }

---

## TESTING RULES

### Before Marking Anything Complete
- Test happy path (everything works)
- Test error path (what if API fails)
- Test empty state (no data)
- Test loading state (slow network)
- Test on mobile (375px width)
- Test with real data (not just mock)

### Common Edge Cases Always Test
- Empty strings submitted in forms
- Very long strings (500+ chars)
- Special characters in inputs
- Double clicking submit button
- Network failure mid-request
- Token expiry during session
- Invalid/expired promo codes
- Out of stock items in cart
- Zero quantity orders

---

## FORBIDDEN PATTERNS

NEVER do these:
  ❌ console.log(password) or any sensitive data
  ❌ process.env.SECRET || 'hardcoded_fallback'
  ❌ any type in TypeScript
  ❌ Inline styles (use Tailwind)
  ❌ Direct DOM manipulation
  ❌ Nested ternaries more than 2 levels
  ❌ Functions longer than 50 lines
  ❌ Files longer than 300 lines (split them)
  ❌ Copy-paste code (extract to function)
  ❌ TODO comments in production code
  ❌ Commented out code blocks
  ❌ Magic numbers without constants
  ❌ Hardcoded restaurant name/address/phone
  ❌ API calls without error handling
  ❌ useEffect without dependency array
  ❌ setState in render (infinite loop)
  ❌ Mutating state directly
  ❌ Missing key prop in lists
